    <pb facs="liv_002435_0001" n="0001"/>

<!-- I have questions for you regarding how to handle the vertical text; the coding guidelines instruct me to end the previous text as a paragraph (even if it's not the end of a paragraph) and open the vertical text as a new paragraph. Do I need to close the vertical text as a paragraph as well, and then reopen the continued horizontal text as a new paragraph? Should I just continue and not mark the continued horizontal text as a new paragraph? -->

<lb/><opener><add place="inline"><gap reason="illegible" extent="4" atLeast="3" atMost="5" unit="chars"/> <unclear cert="medium">Village</unclear> 4</add><space extent="1" unit="chars"/> <dateline><placeName>Bombay</placeName> <date when="1865-11-17">17 <choice><abbr>Nov.</abbr><expan>November</expan></choice><hi rend="sup"><unclear cert="low">br</unclear></hi> 1865</date></dateline>
<lb/><add place="inline" rend="gray vertical large diagonal">42</add>
<lb/><measure>CCCXXXIX</measure><!-- The number is 329, and I have no idea what it could be referring to. Considering a measurement for the time being. BL.--> <space extent="1" unit="chars"/><add place="inline" rend="blue">14</add><!-- number is circled. Not sure how to code. BL. -->
<lb/></opener>
<lb/><ab>My Dearest <persName>Annie</persName></ab><!-- having this line in opener makes it appear at the bottom and messes with format/size. Using <ab> seems to work just fine. BL -->

<p rend="left"><lb/><space extent="1" unit="words"/>You have hit on an
<lb/>admirable plan, and here
<lb/>you see the influence of good
<lb/>example for I have adopted
<lb/>it too. I have duly received
<lb/>your III and as <persName><choice><abbr>M<hi rend="sup">s</hi></abbr><expan>Miss</expan></choice> Stearns</persName>
<lb/>despatches a ship on the <date when="1865-11-20">20<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date>
<lb/>to <settlement type="city">Suez</settlement> I begin a note to be
<lb/>in <unclear>need of men</unclear> for that occurs
<lb/><unclear cert="low">on</unclear> I am getting very uneasy
<lb/>to be off - no word has yet
<lb/>come from the <term type="occupation">Admiral</term> and
<lb/>as I am all ready to start I
<lb/>am not at all reconciled
<lb/>to delay - I have <measure>12</measure> men of
<lb/>the <term type="occupation">Marines</term> &amp; <placeName>Mavildar</placeName> a
<lb/><orgName>native</orgName> officer ready to go
<lb/>at a moment's notice - Then
<lb/><measure>8</measure> <orgName>Africans</orgName> from <placeName>Nassick</placeName><!--Not sure if they're "from" a village named Nassick or from a person names as such. BL> --> </p> 
<lb/>
<p><lb/><cb rend="vertical"></cb>Love to <unclear><persName>Madline</persName></unclear> tocédé<unclear> <!-- French for Tobacco? Best I can come up with. BL. !--></unclear></p>

    <pb facs="liv_002435_0002" n="0002"/>

<p><lb/>a Government school for
<lb/>the education of captured &amp;
<lb/>liberated <orgName>Africans</orgName> - <measure>Five</measure> more
<lb/>from the <placeName><geogName type="river">Zambesi</geogName></placeName> go part
<lb/>of the way, and <measure>two</measure> boys
<lb/>whom we once gave to 
<lb/><persName>Bishop Mackenzie</persName> - They
<lb/>have been at <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Wilson's</persName>
<lb/>school here and have picked
<lb/>up <term type="language">English</term> - <unclear cert="low">to indo ostance</unclear><!-- currently can't gleam any concrete words from this. BL. -->
<lb/>and <term type="language">Marathi</term> so as to speak
<lb/>a little of each - They read
<lb/>English pretty well &amp; <persName><choice><abbr>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi></abbr><expan>Doctor</expan></choice> Wilson</persName>
<lb/>thinks that they are fit for
<lb/>baptism. This is pretty well
<lb/>for <measure>15 months</measure> education
<lb/>One of them named <persName>Chuma</persName>
<lb/>wrote a letter to <persName>Waller</persName> - and
<lb/>the address was - <persName><choice><abbr>M<hi rend="sup">s</hi></abbr><expan>Miss</expan></choice> Waller</persName> <persName>Chuma</persName><!-- currently putting text in-line, even though "Chuma" is practcally in the line below. BL. Unable to mark with <query> without splitting it up, and using <lb/> was convoluted. Edit as fit. BL.-->
<lb/>Those will form
<lb/>the party say <measure>23</measure> - I have got
<lb/>several volunteers <unclear>in hudra</unclear><!--No clue. BL.-->
<lb/>but declined them. If I had
<lb/><persName><choice><abbr>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi></abbr><expan>Doctor</expan></choice> Kirk</persName> it would be different
<lb/>but untried men are often a
<lb/>nuisance. <measure>Fo<add place="below">^</add><add place="above">u</add>rteen</measure> <term type="animal">buffaloes</term></p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p><cb rend="vertical"></cb><persName><choice><abbr>M<hi rend="sup">s</hi></abbr><expan>Miss</expan></choice> Stearns</persName> is an active <term type="nationality">American</term> <term type="occupation">merchant</term></p>


    <pb facs="liv_002435_0003" n="0003"/>

<lb/><p rend="no-indent">and the <term type="animal">calves</term> are sent
<lb/>off already - and should an
<lb/>opportunity occur for me
<lb/>to go I shall follow- I am
<lb/>all ready.</p>
<lb/><p>I went up <measure>300 miles</measure>
<lb/>in <placeName><choice><orig>Goozerat</orig><reg>Gujarat</reg></choice></placeName> - &amp; I think
<lb/>sent my <measure>338</measure> from <settlement type="city">Surat</settlement>
<lb/>as well as one to <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi>Webb</persName>
<lb/>in answer to what I received
<lb/>from her- The country was
<lb/>just like <placeName><bloc>Africa</bloc></placeName>- plants &amp;
<lb/>trees nearly identical - I saw
<lb/>the buildings of which I
<lb/>saw the photographs last
<lb/>time I went down to <persName><choice><abbr>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi></abbr><expan>Mister</expan></choice>
<lb/>Murray's</persName> at <settlement type="city">Wimbledon</settlement> - 
<lb/>They are very fine, and
<lb/>the carving is wonderfully
<lb/>elaborate - The city of
<lb/><choice><orig><placeName><settlement type="city">Ahmeda-bad</settlement></placeName></orig><reg>Ahmedabad</reg></choice> in which they
<lb/>are found is <unclear>around old I</unclear>
<lb/><unclear cert="low">Wilson</unclear> one and a week
<lb/>would have been well
<lb/>spent in <unclear cert="low">warming</unclear> up them
<lb/>but I felt so anxious to be</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p><cb rend="vertical"></cb>His father a professor - in a college - a brother
<lb/>was killed in the war - good people <persName><choice><orig>alex</orig><reg>Alex</reg></choice></persName></p>
    
    <pb facs="liv_002435_0004" n="0004"/>

<lb/><p rend="no-indent">away from this that I spent
<lb/>only one day - I saw a <orgName>native</orgName>
<lb/><term type="faith">Christian</term> village and was
<lb/>gratified by the pleasant
<lb/>expression of the women's
<lb/>faces - The several appearance<supplied>s</supplied>
<lb/>of the same clans but of heathen
<lb/>women is not pleasing -
<lb/>After service on <date when="1865-11-12">Sunday</date>
<lb/>morning one came <w>for-
<lb break="no"/>ward</w> &amp; said she did not like
<lb/>to see us going away <unclear cert="medium">&amp; basting</unclear><!-- my best guess is that she didn't like to seem them go as if they had just had a beating (an obsolete use of baste). BL.-->
<lb/>would we take <term type="foodstuff">tea</term> or <term type="foodstuff">milk</term> -
<lb/>I chose the latter and she gave
<lb/>me a cup of <term type="animal">buffaloe</term>'s <term type="foodstuff">milk</term>
<lb/>which is very white - and so
<lb/>is the butter but it is <w>pre-
<lb break="no"/>-ferred</w> to <term type="animal">cow</term>'s here - You see
<lb/>the <term type ="animal">buffaloes</term> lying in the water
<lb/>during the day with their heads
<lb/>only above the surface - I
<lb/>stopped a day with <persName><choice><abbr>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>Mister</expan></choice> Taylor</persName>
<lb/>he is quite alone as his wife
<lb/>had to leave from bad health-
<lb/>I was disappointed in not
<lb/>meeting a <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">rs</hi>Oliphant</persName>'s daugt<supplied>er</supplied>
<lb/>of <term type="occupation">General</term> <persName>Alexander <unclear>Wilson</unclear></persName></p>


            </div>
